Anonymous Wed 23 May 2018 18:36:12 No.15948870 Report
Quoted By: >>15948895
so someone in the last thread posted about how they hate how most all of these issues are in second person perspective. I completely understand, and though the novelty of the format hasn't worn off for me as a reader, I know that for those of you who have read a lot of them might not enjoy it as much as I do still. however, I'm currently in the middle of writing a story (non-prompted), and seeing anon's comment about the second person perspective made me think. I started to think about writing the story in a third person, non-greentext format, how I could change the language and sentences to accompany the more traditional styling. but reading through it, I realized that there's really no way to do so. the greentext format, while a bit overdone, lends itself to a way of dictation and speaking that is so much different from other ways. it's like trying to turn an apple into an orange. so, while I agree the format is overdone, I don't think we should discount it entirely. the sentence structure you can make and use with it is so much different from first or third perspective, and it's honestly a little... liberating, strangely.

tl;dr sure greentext is kinda the default 'mode' here, but just because it's overdone doesn't mean it doesn't have merit. just means that people need to write differently sometimes.
